This article is a transcript of remarks made by the President at the Daytona International Speedway for the 62nd Daytona 500. The President expressed his excitement to join the race fans and highlighted the importance of God, family, and country in NASCAR. He also acknowledged the presence of Gold Star Families and honored their fallen warriors. The President thanked Staff Sergeant David Bellavia, who received the Congressional Medal of Honor, and congratulated new enlistees in the United States Armed Forces. He expressed gratitude to all service members and veterans and emphasized the strength of the US military. The President then mentioned the start of the race and wished good luck to the drivers, technicians, and pit crews. He concluded by giving thanks for the country, the heroes who keep it safe, and the God who made it free.